Cut the watermelon flesh into chunks and, working in batches, puree in a blender until liquified, Strain through a fine sieve to remove the pulp; you should have about 4 cups of juice. Combine the watermelon juice and the lemonade in a 5-quart pitcher. To make individual cocktails. fill a shaker with ice. Add 1 cup of the watermelon-lemonade mixture and 2 ounces of alcohol. Shake vigorously. Strain into a tall glass filled with ice or a chilled martini glass.